        "faq_section_main": {
          "type": "faq_section",
          "settings": {
            "q1": "Will it turn my skin green or tarnish?",
            "a1": "<p>No. This bracelet is made from premium surgical-grade steel with 14K gold PVD plating. It is tarnish-resistant and corrosion-proof. It won't turn green fade or lose its shine even with daily wear.</p>",
            "q2": "Can I wear it in the shower or swimming?",
            "a2": "<p>Yes. The stainless steel construction and PVD coating make it fully waterproof. You can shower swim and exercise without ever taking it off.</p>",
            "q3": "Is it safe for sensitive skin?",
            "a3": "<p>Absolutely. It is 100% hypoallergenic \u2014 nickel-free and lead-free. Designed specifically for people with metal sensitivities.</p>",
            "q4": "Will it fit my wrist?",
            "a4": "<p>The bracelet is 17cm with a 5cm extension chain so it adjusts to fit wrists from 17cm to 22cm. This covers most wrist sizes from S to XL.</p>",
            "q5": "What is the difference between Gold and Silver?",
            "a5": "<p>Both are made from the same premium surgical-grade steel. Gold has a 14K gold PVD plating with warm gold tones. Silver has a high-polished chrome finish. Both are equally durable and tarnish-resistant.</p>",
            "q6": "Is this a good gift?",
            "a6": "<p>It is one of our best-selling gift items. The infinity love knot symbolizes eternal love and connection \u2014 perfect for anniversaries birthdays Valentine's Day Mother's Day or bridesmaid gifts. Comes in premium gift-ready packaging.</p>",
            "q7": "How does it compare to designer jewelry?",
            "a7": "<p>Similar infinity knot bracelets from designer brands cost $175-$400. This bracelet uses the same 316L stainless steel and delivers the same premium look and durability for under $25. The difference is the brand name not the quality.</p>",
